        "URL": "data:text/html;charset=utf-8,%3C!doctype%20html%3E%0A%3Chtml%20lang%3D%22%22%3E%0A%3Chead%3E%0A%20%20%3Cmeta%20charset%3D%22utf-8%22%3E%0A%20%20%3Ctitle%3EHysteresis%20Epsilon%20Expansion%3C%2Ftitle%3E%0A%3C%2Fhead%3E%0A%3Cbody%3E%0A%3Cbody%3E%0A%0A%3Ch1%3EThe%20Epsilon%20Expansion%20for%20Hysteresis%20(Dahmen%2C%20Perkovic'%3B%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fpub.html%2366%22%3E66%2C%2068%2C%2069%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fpub.html%2375%22%3E%2075%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fh1%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%0ACan%20we%20give%20a%20theoretical%20description%20of%20why%20we%20get%20power%20laws%20and%0Ascaling%2C%20beyond%20analogies%20to%20equilibrium%20critical%20phenomena%3F%20%20We%20found%20a%0Amean-field%20theory%20for%20the%20problem%2C%20valid%20above%20dimension%20%3Cem%3Ed%3D6%3C%2Fem%3E.%0AThen%20Karin%20Dahmen%20and%20I%20produced%20a%20expansion%20for%20the%20critical%20exponents%0Aas%20a%20function%20of%20%3Cem%3Eepsilon%20%3D%206-d%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%20This%20problem%20turns%20out%20to%20be%0Asimpler%20in%20many%20ways%20than%20the%20expansion%20for%20depinning%20transitions%20we%0Abased%20our%20methods%20on%2C%20so%20our%20results%20were%20correspondingly%20more%20complete%3A%0ADahmen%20has%20been%20able%20to%20both%20(a)%20calculate%20the%20avalanche%20critical%0Aexponents%20%3Cem%3Etau%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Esigma%3C%2Fem%3E%20explicitly%2C%20to%0A%3Cem%3EO(epsilon)%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20(b)%20map%20the%20expansion%20for%20the%20traditional%0Aexponents%20%3Cem%3Ebeta%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Edelta%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Enu%3C%2Fem%3E%20onto%20the%0Acalculation%20for%20the%20pure%20Ising%20model%20in%20two%20lower%20dimensions.%20%20Olga%0APerkovi%60c%20and%20Karin%20and%20I%20have%20been%20running%20extensive%20numerical%0Asimulations%20to%20test%20these%20exponents%20in%20dimensions%20%3Cem%3Ed%3D3%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%0A%3Cem%3E4%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3E5%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%20The%20agreement%20is%20excellent.%0A%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22Exponents_paper_new_vertical.ps%22%3E%20%0A%3Cimg%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%20%0A%3Cstrong%3ENumerical%20values%20of%20the%20universal%20critical%20exponents%2C%20compared%0Ato%20the%20predictions%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Eepsilon%3C%2Fem%3E-expansion%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20%0A%3Cem%3EThe%20numerical%20values%20were%20derived%20from%20hundreds%20of%20runs%20of%20sizes%0A%3Cem%3E320%5E3%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3E80%5E4%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3E30%5E5%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20the%20dashed%20lines%20are%0Apredictions%20of%20our%20%3Cem%3Eepsilon%3C%2Fem%3E-expansion%20to%20linear%20order%20in%0A%3Cem%3Eepsilon%20%3D%206-d%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20dotted%20line%20is%20our%20Borel%20re-summation%20of%20the%0A%3Cem%3Eepsilon%3C%2Fem%3E%20expansion%20for%20%3Cem%3E1%2Fnu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20is%20known%20(from%20the%0Amapping%20to%20the%20pure%20Ising%20model)%20to%20%3Cem%3Eepsilon%5E5%3C%2Fem%3E.%0A%0A%3C%2Fem%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2Fhysteresis.html%22%3E%0AMore%20Information%20about%20Hysteresis%20and%20Avalanches%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%0A%3Cul%20compact%3D%22%22%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2Fauthors.html%22%3E%0AAuthors%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2Fhysteresis.html%22%3E%0AHysteresis%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2FWhatIsHysteresis.html%22%3E%0AWhat%20is%20Hysteresis%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2Fnoise.html%22%3E%0ANoise%20in%20Hysteresis%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2FReturnPointMemory.html%22%3E%0AReturn%20Point%20Memory%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fseth